Specific Claims Provisions 
In the event of a claim the Insured Person must: 
1) give immediate written notice: 
a) to the relevant Common Carrier in the event of loss or damage in transit; 
b) to the relevant police authority in the event of loss or theft; 

2) submit a copy of the relevant Common Carrier or police report when a claim is made; 

3) obtain a Common Carrier or police report where the loss occurred; 

4) in the event of loss by a Common Carrier, retain original tickets and baggage slips and submit them when 
